<subSubSection id="2174B26F0A0630942D793A6B1DD38D0A" pageId="17" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F8074FB476BC97F607778D8BCEB42A57" pageId="17" pageNumber="32">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="69D1F038C371380CCA5B2F0E822BF1EF" pageId="17" pageNumber="32">
This species has been recorded in Egypt (the Sinai Peninsula) and Israel. Notwithstanding, 
<bibRefCitation id="127DFC41EB26DECB2C6BACBA87841E94" author="Kovarik, F" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="29" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 16" title="Review of Tunisian Species of the Genus Buthus with Descriptions of Two New Species and a Discussion of Ehrenberg's Types (Scorpiones: Buthidae)." url="http://www.science.marshall.edu/fet/euscorpius/p2006_34.pdf" volume="34" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="C983DC1D6C3140F8A081825A8B178CBC" originalValue="Kovařík">Kovarik</normalizedToken>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
considered this species to be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="28351E66BA256357B6174FAE2A974BD3" genus="B." lsidName="B. intumescens" pageId="17" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="intumescens">B. intumescens</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
